EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

Description of Facility and Regulated Substance Handled:
Oberweis Dairies, 951 Ice Cream Drive Sweet One, North Aurora, Illinois 60542 processes ice cream products and dairy products. The facility utilizes anhydrous ammonia as a refrigerant to maintain the proper temperature of ice cream and dairy products within the facility. Anhydrous ammonia is an effective refrigerant that has been used for many years by most food processing facilities. Ammonia is normally a gas at ambient temperatures but is handled as a gas liquefied under pressure. The refrigeration system consists of a receiver vessel, condensers, evaporators, compressors, piping, and valves.

A Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Oberweis Dairy, Inc. (Oberweis) facility located at 951 Ice Cream Drive in North Aurora, Illinois, for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This updated, five (5) year Risk Management Plan (RMP) summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including: 
A?    Introduction;
A?    Oberweis policies to protect health, environment, and safety;
A?    Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;
A?    Hazard Assessment;
A?    Prevention Program;
A?    Five-Year Accident History;
A?    Emergency Response Plan; 
A?    Emergency Communications;
A?    Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;
A?    Planned changes to improve safety; and
A?    Management Program

Oberweis Policies To Protect Health, Environment, and Safety
Risk management and safety are important concerns at Oberweis; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. Oberweis is committed to conducting its operations
